cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on teaching motion to robotic systems using imitation learning and proposes a framework for modeling demonstrated trajectories with a neural network. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a neural network structure built on the variational autoencoder (VAE) for learning the low-dimensional latent space of the robot trajectory. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses a trajectory augmentation technique inspired by the data augmentation commonly used in the computer vision community to cope with the requirement of massive training data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a motion planner using the learned decoder that can be used to tune the trajectory in an intuitive manner even when the user is an expert. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper addresses the problem of modifying the planned trajectory of a robotic manipulator, which is related to the field of systems and control.
